annotation_set.note:
LRG_804 ACHE Polymorphisms in LRG_804, ACHE give rise to antigenic variants of the Yt blood group system, Yt (ISBT 011). The sequences in this LRG record represent the YT*01 allele (haplotype) (1). ---.
The transcript NM_015831.2 (previously used as the reference transcript) has been suppressed by the NCBI. A review of NM_015831.2 found that the transcript model had been built on a synthetic construct and did not have full length support.
NM_015831.2 has been replaced by NM_001302621.1 which encodes for the same protein and differs only in a splice acceptor site in the 5' UTR.
The older ISBT table (1) has been updated (2) to refer to NM_001302621.1, but the c. numbering has remained unchanged.
NM_001302621.1/NP_001289550.1 is the dominant form expressed in erythroid cells, and is not the dominant form expressed in other tissues e.g. the brain.
---. REFERENCES. 1) International Society for Blood Transfusion (ISBT) allele tables, YT (ISBT 011) blood group alleles v4.0 160630. 2) International Society for Blood Transfusion (ISBT) allele tables, YT (ISBT 011) blood group alleles v5.0 180207. http://www.isbtweb.org/working-parties/red-cell-immunogenetics-and-blood-group-terminology/
